  "text": "The purpose of this paper is to assess the performance of RCAs, which have been in place for approximately a decade (from 7 to 11 years), and provide recommendations for improvements. We used the design principles highlighted by [CITATION_1] as key aspects of sustainable resource management to assess the ecological and social performance of RCAs based on studies conducted to date. RCAs are faced with many of the same issues as other fisheries closures and marine conservation areas are (e.g., social buy-in, compliance, enforcement, monitoring); hence, their assessment has the potential to provide lessons for current and future marine conservation areas. Additionally, we assess the usefulness and applicability of scaling up the design principles for federally managed resource systems.",
  "correct_citation": {
